<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-26T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="644" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">760F.62/1147k: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-27T01:00:00+01:00">September 27, 1938—1
                                    a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>564. The President would be interested to know if Chamberlain has
                            received a reply from Hitler to the personal letter Chamberlain wrote
                            him and which was delivered by Sir Horace Wilson.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>